# sitio-design-notes Development Guidelines

Auto-generated from all feature plans. Last updated: 2026-04-02

## Active Technologies
- PostgreSQL 14+; local dev assumed at `localhost:5432`; schema and migrations via Prisma (001-school-trip-payments)

- TypeScript 5.x (dashboard and backend), Node.js LTS (align with TanStack Start and NestJS supported ranges at implementation time) + Dashboard: TanStack Start (SPA), TanStack Router, TanStack Query, TanStack Form, shadcn/ui (Base UI preset), Zod, Zustand, Vite tooling as provided by the Start template. Backend: NestJS, @nestjs/cqrs, Prisma, class-validator/class-transformer or Zod at boundary as chosen per module, pg driver via Prisma (001-school-trip-payments)

## Project Structure

```text
specs/<feature>/
├── spec.md, plan.md, research.md, data-model.md, quickstart.md, contracts/
Implementation: ../sitio-dashboard (TanStack Start SPA + shadcn), ../sitio-backend (NestJS CQRS + Prisma)
```

## Commands

This repo (specs only): `yamllint` / markdown review as needed.  
Dashboard (`../sitio-dashboard`): `pnpm install`, `pnpm dev`, `pnpm test`, `pnpm lint` (after scaffold).  
Backend (`../sitio-backend`): `pnpm install`, `pnpm start:dev`, `pnpm test`, `pnpm exec prisma migrate dev` (human-run migrations).

## Code Style

TypeScript 5.x (dashboard and backend), Node.js LTS (align with TanStack Start and NestJS supported ranges at implementation time): Follow standard conventions

